item.title: Changing map data on 317 client
item.dc:creator: @doom_j doom_j
item.description:
@doom_j wrote:

[quote=“supra s, post:12, topic:252089”]
DOWNLOAD 1.1

Requirements :

For adding loader : Basic C/P ,and Windows Explorer usage, knowing where your cache is.

For editing maps: A mouse and JAVA.

Adding maploader:
You`ll need FileOperations.java , to get it look at the end of the post

Step 0:

Replace your mapeditor.jar in mapeditor home with mapeditor.jar from download, you need the mapedit files from 1.0 download

Step 1:
Find in client.java:

if(abyte0 != null) class7.method180(abyte0, k5, i4, (anInt1069 - 6) * 8, (anInt1070 - 6) * 8, (byte)4, aClass11Array1230);

Add this above it:

if (FileOperations.FileExists(signlink.findcachedir()+"maps/"+anIntArray1235[i3]+".dat")) abyte0 = FileOperations.ReadFile(signlink.findcachedir()+"maps/"+anIntArray1235[i3]+".dat");

Steo 2:
Find this in client.java:

class7.method183(aClass11Array1230, aClass25_946, k10, j8 * 8, (i12 & 7) * 8, true, l6, aByteArrayArray1247[k12], (k11 & 7) * 8, i11, j9 * 8);
Replace with:

[CODE] byte abyte0[] = aByteArrayArray1247[k12];
if (FileOperations.FileExists(signlink.findcachedir()+“maps/”+anIntArray1235[k12]+".dat")) abyte0 = FileOperations.ReadFile(signlink.findcachedir()+“maps/”+anIntArray1235[k12]+".dat");

                                class7.method183(aClass11Array1230, aClass25_946, k10, j8 * 8, (i12 & 7) * 8, true, l6, abyte0, (k11 & 7) * 8, i11, j9 * 8);
                 [/CODE]

Step 3:
Create a directory named maps in your cache directory.

Credits : JAGeX for the mapformat and client, Mopar for the renamed client.

you need some extra files but they are located on a other site to lazy to post xD

CREDITS TO Cocoa end peterbjornx (google)[/quote]
